FBIS4-54375 "dreas103__a94001" FBIS-EAS-94-103-A Daily Report 26 May 1994 ANNEX Cambodia KR `Defectors' Say Pol Pot Living in Thailand KR `Defectors' Say Pol Pot Living in Thailand BK2005075794 Hong Kong FAR EASTERN ECONOMIC REVIEW in English 26 May 94 p 12 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY BK2005075794 Hong Kong FAR EASTERN ECONOMIC REVIEW English BFN [From the "Intelligence" column] [Text] Elusive Khmer Rouge supremo Pol Pot has moved house again. Khmer Rouge [KR] defectors reported that after spending some time in a special residence in Phnum Chhat area near the Thai border in late 1993, Pol Pot moved to the safety of Thailand. He is believed to living in a well-guarded compound inside a durian plantation near the provincial capital, Chanthaburi. For a number of years in the late 1980s, Pol Pot had lived in a compound called "Zone 87" in Trat province bordering Cambodia.
